-- Richter Falls Most in Seven Weeks on Forest Labs: Budapest Mover
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2013-01-15T17:05:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/richter-falls-most-in-seven-weeks-on-forest-labs-budapest-mover.html
Gedeon  Richter Nyrt ., Hungary’s
biggest drugmaker, fell the most in seven weeks after a loss
reported by its U.S. drug development partner  Forest
Laboratories Inc. (FRX)  exceeded analyst estimates.  Richter’s shares slid 1.7 percent to 37,100 forint by the
close in Budapest, the steepest decline since Nov. 27. Forest
slipped as much as 3.7 percent and traded 0.1 percent lower at
$37.55 by 11:21 a.m. in New York.  Forest’s loss in the quarter ended Dec. 31 was 21 cents a
share excluding one-time items, the New York-based drugmaker
said in a statement today. That compares with an 8-cent loss
that was the average of 23 analyst estimates compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
